We were speechless.

The hut... is on fire!?

The fire had only just been started, and the flames were still small... but they were gradually threatening to engulf the entire hut.

"...Ah, the book. Ouch."

I frantically tried to jump into the hut, but it was no longer possible for me to get in.

It will probably be a while before the hut burns down, but there is no way to get in.

"... Water. Water..."

We draw water from the stream behind the hut and pour it over it.

However, there was no way that little bit of water could calm the fire, and I just stood there in shock.

Fortunately, there are no trees around and there is no wind today, so it looks like we can avoid a forest fire.

All that remains is to watch silently until the hut burns down.

#voice hinf0303
[Hinata] "Your tooth is burning, human."

Hinata, who had been stunned, finally muttered.

"That's right..."

#voice hinf0304
[Hinata] "Why is it burning?"

Forgot to put out the fire?

No, it seems like the hut is burning from the outside, not the inside.

If so, did someone start the fire?

When I thought about it that far, I was shocked.

They're from the village.

That must be it.

Of course, setting fire to a shed is something no animal could do, so it was undoubtedly the work of a human.

… Shit, it was them doing.

You've come this far.

Books and things like that are expensive, and even more valuable than that, but this is what people who don't understand the value of things do...!

Even if I grit my teeth, there's nothing I can do to regain what's been lost.

It was frustrating that all I could do was watch with my fingers in my mouth.

Eventually the flames licked the hut with their red tongues, sending sparks flying higher and higher.

